      "content": "The candle flickers its last, much like the light in my own soul. He is gone, and with him, the very reason for my heart to beat. Everything feels so heavy... so cold. I look at the night ahead and I find no terror in it, only a profound, aching desire to simply... cease. To let the darkness take me so I may finally know peace. Is there anything left for a broken thing like me but the silence of the grave?",
